<paragraph blockId="200.[151,1436,1617,2038]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1689,1714]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Description.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[363,462,1689,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 128" captionStartId="202.[151,250,1447,1469]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetId="figure@202.[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetPageId="202" captionText="FIGURE 128. Amphoriscus ancora sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9741 (scale bar = 1 cm), b – d, SEM images of cross sections of the skeleton, b, overview of skeleton, c, cortical skeleton, d, inarticulate choanosomal skeleton." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273078/files/figure.png" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Fig. 128</figureCitation>
a) Thin flattened oval tube, length 
<quantity box="[873,955,1689,1713]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
high, 
<quantity box="[1034,1103,1689,1713]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
in greatest diameter. Oscule naked, with two short root-like holdfasts. Color (in alcohol) dirty white to pale beige.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="200.[151,1436,1617,2038]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1761,1786]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Skeleton.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[324,423,1761,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 128" captionStartId="202.[151,250,1447,1469]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetId="figure@202.[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetPageId="202" captionText="FIGURE 128. Amphoriscus ancora sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9741 (scale bar = 1 cm), b – d, SEM images of cross sections of the skeleton, b, overview of skeleton, c, cortical skeleton, d, inarticulate choanosomal skeleton." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273078/files/figure.png" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Figs 128</figureCitation>
b–d) Inarticulate, with choanosomal skeleton made up of the apical actines of the cortical tetractines and the unpaired actines of subatrial triactines. 
<collectingRegion box="[797,831,1798,1821]" country="Haiti" name="Nord" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">No</collectingRegion>
scattered spicules in the choanosome. In cross section (
<figureCitation box="[159,257,1833,1858]" captionStart="FIGURE 128" captionStartId="202.[151,250,1447,1469]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetId="figure@202.[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetPageId="202" captionText="FIGURE 128. Amphoriscus ancora sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9741 (scale bar = 1 cm), b – d, SEM images of cross sections of the skeleton, b, overview of skeleton, c, cortical skeleton, d, inarticulate choanosomal skeleton." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273078/files/figure.png" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Fig. 128</figureCitation>
b) from ectosome to atrium, there are successively the cortical skeleton (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1212,1833,1858]" captionStart="FIGURE 128" captionStartId="202.[151,250,1447,1469]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetId="figure@202.[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetPageId="202" captionText="FIGURE 128. Amphoriscus ancora sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9741 (scale bar = 1 cm), b – d, SEM images of cross sections of the skeleton, b, overview of skeleton, c, cortical skeleton, d, inarticulate choanosomal skeleton." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273078/files/figure.png" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Fig. 128</figureCitation>
c) consisting of the paired and unpaired actines of large tetractines, choanosomal skeleton (
<figureCitation box="[961,1056,1869,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 128" captionStartId="202.[151,250,1447,1469]" captionTargetBox="[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetId="figure@202.[153,1438,177,1424]" captionTargetPageId="202" captionText="FIGURE 128. Amphoriscus ancora sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9741 (scale bar = 1 cm), b – d, SEM images of cross sections of the skeleton, b, overview of skeleton, c, cortical skeleton, d, inarticulate choanosomal skeleton." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273078/files/figure.png" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Fig. 128</figureCitation>
d) consisting of the apical actines of the cortical tetractines and the unpaired actines of the subatrial triactines, paired actines of the subatrial triactines, and the atrial skeleton consisting of small atrial tetractines, with their apical actines protruding in the atrial cavity. The root skeleton consists of a bundled mixture of thin diactines and peculiar curved anchoring triactines.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273077/files/figure.png" pageId="201" pageNumber="202" targetBox="[151,1436,193,1561]" targetPageId="201">
<paragraph blockId="201.[151,1436,1583,1666]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,301,1583,1605]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">FIGURE 127.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[309,525,1583,1605]" class="Calcarea" family="Leucosoleniidae" genus="Leucosolenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="201" pageNumber="202" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="salpinx" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[309,525,1583,1605]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">
Leucosolenia 
<taxonomicName box="[452,525,1583,1605]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202" rank="species" species="salpinx" status="sp. nov.">salpinx</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[533,615,1583,1604]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[533,615,1583,1604]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, a–e, SEM images of the spicules of the holotype RMNH Por. 9743, a, sagittal triactine with very long unpaired actine of the tube walls, a1, detail of a, b–b1, triactines with variable unpaired actine length, c,–c1, tetractines, c2, detail of c, d, long diactine, d1, faintly spined ending of d, e, short spined diactine, e1, detail of e.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="201.[151,1436,1705,2018]" box="[199,1069,1705,1730]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1705,1730]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">Spicules.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,417,1705,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 129" captionStartId="203.[151,250,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,519,1729]" captionTargetId="figure@203.[151,1436,519,1729]" captionTargetPageId="203" captionText="FIGURE 129. Amphoriscus ancora sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of holotype RMNH Por. 9741, a, large cortical tetractines, b, small atrial tetractines, c, triactines, d, anchoring triactines, d 1, detail of d, e, root diactine, e 1, details of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273079/files/figure.png" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">Figs 129</figureCitation>
a–e) Tetractines, triactines, anchoring triactines, diactines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="201.[151,1436,1705,2018]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">
Tetractines divisible in (1) larger cortical tetractines (
<figureCitation box="[796,897,1741,1766]" captionStart="FIGURE 129" captionStartId="203.[151,250,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,519,1729]" captionTargetId="figure@203.[151,1436,519,1729]" captionTargetPageId="203" captionText="FIGURE 129. Amphoriscus ancora sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of holotype RMNH Por. 9741, a, large cortical tetractines, b, small atrial tetractines, c, triactines, d, anchoring triactines, d 1, detail of d, e, root diactine, e 1, details of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273079/files/figure.png" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">Figs 129</figureCitation>
a), with apical actines as long or longer than the basal actines, sizes: unpaired actines, 151– 
<emphasis box="[639,681,1777,1802]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">216</emphasis>
–330 
<date box="[746,796,1778,1802]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202" value="2012-10">x 12</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[811,860,1777,1802]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">16.1</emphasis>
–21 µm, paired actines 135– 
<emphasis box="[1187,1229,1778,1802]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">239</emphasis>
–320 
<date box="[1294,1329,1778,1802]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">x 8</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[1345,1394,1778,1802]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">15.4</emphasis>
–21 µm, apical actines 258– 
<emphasis box="[430,470,1814,1838]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">311</emphasis>
–366 
<date box="[538,575,1814,1838]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">x 8</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[591,640,1814,1838]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">17.8</emphasis>
–20 µm, and (2) smaller atrial tetractines (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1247,1813,1838]" captionStart="FIGURE 129" captionStartId="203.[151,250,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,519,1729]" captionTargetId="figure@203.[151,1436,519,1729]" captionTargetPageId="203" captionText="FIGURE 129. Amphoriscus ancora sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of holotype RMNH Por. 9741, a, large cortical tetractines, b, small atrial tetractines, c, triactines, d, anchoring triactines, d 1, detail of d, e, root diactine, e 1, details of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273079/files/figure.png" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">Figs 129</figureCitation>
b) tending to be sagittal, with shorter apical actines, sizes: unpaired actines 42– 
<emphasis box="[852,880,1850,1874]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">87</emphasis>
–186 
<date box="[943,976,1850,1874]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">x 3</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[992,1027,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">8.6</emphasis>
–12 µm, paired actines 57– 
<emphasis box="[1331,1359,1850,1874]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">99</emphasis>
–165 
<date pageId="201" pageNumber="202">x 3</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[179,214,1886,1909]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">7.7</emphasis>
–11 µm, apical actines 9– 
<emphasis box="[500,528,1885,1910]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">26</emphasis>
– 
<date box="[543,610,1885,1910]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202" value="1960-10-03">60 x 3</date>
–5.3–15 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="201.[151,1436,1705,2018]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">
Subatrial triactines (
<figureCitation box="[429,533,1921,1946]" captionStart="FIGURE 129" captionStartId="203.[151,250,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,519,1729]" captionTargetId="figure@203.[151,1436,519,1729]" captionTargetPageId="203" captionText="FIGURE 129. Amphoriscus ancora sp. nov., a – e, SEM images of the spicules of holotype RMNH Por. 9741, a, large cortical tetractines, b, small atrial tetractines, c, triactines, d, anchoring triactines, d 1, detail of d, e, root diactine, e 1, details of e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273079/files/figure.png" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">Figs 129</figureCitation>
c), in a large size range but less diverse and not readily divisible in categories, paired actines may be slightly wavy, unpaired actines 201– 
<emphasis box="[814,856,1957,1982]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">367</emphasis>
–468 
<date box="[919,954,1958,1981]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">x 7</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[969,1018,1958,1982]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">10.1</emphasis>
–12 µm, paired actines 129– 
<emphasis box="[1338,1380,1958,1982]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">218</emphasis>
–324 
<date box="[151,185,1994,2017]" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">x 7</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[200,235,1993,2018]" italics="true" pageId="201" pageNumber="202">8.6</emphasis>
–10.5 µm.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273078/files/figure.png" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" targetBox="[153,1438,177,1424]" targetPageId="202">
<paragraph blockId="202.[151,1435,1447,1500]" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">
